1. Capitalisation per NOSM, particularly 5.3.1.
2. Solidus - space each side, for consistency with cases where that's needed for layout.
3. Section headings: title case
4. Subsection headings: title case
5. Lower level headings: sentence case.
6. Parenthetical dash: open en-rule (general UK usage) not closed em-rule (OUP & US)
7. Bullet etc. lists. Entries only capitalised if full sentences. Otherwise separated by semicolons.